     The aallaarrmm() function waits a count of _s_e_c_o_n_d_s before asserting the
     terminating signal SIGALRM. When the signal has successfully been caught,
     aallaarrmm() returns the amount of time left on the clock.  The maximum mumber
     of _s_e_c_o_n_d_s allowed is 2147483647.

     If an alarm has been set with aallaarrmm(), another call to aallaarrmm() will
     superceed the prior call.  The request aallaarrmm(_0) voids the current alarm.

